FBIS4-63256 "drsov098_f_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 National Affairs Black Sea Fleet Threatens To Intervene in Crimea Black Sea Fleet Threatens To Intervene in Crimea AU2005100694 Paris AFP in English 0952 GMT 20 May 94 AU2005100694 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Sevastopol, Ukraine, May 20 (AFP) -- The Black Sea Fleet, shared between the Ukraine and Russia, threatened Friday [20 May] to intervene in Crimea after the region's parliament adopted a new constitution effectively declaring independence from Kiev. "It is clear that whatever the development of the situation, the Black Sea Fleet cannot remain outside events unfolding around it," the Fleet's Press Office said in a statement.
